Indonesia Stocks: Hexindo, International Nickel, Trada Maritime

-- B y   B e r n i   M o e s t a f a
-- 
2011-09-09T04:57:54Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-09/indonesia-stocks-astra-agro-lestari-hexindo-adiperkasa-trada.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in Indonesian trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the 11:30 a.m. Jakarta-time
break.  The  Jakarta Composite index (JCI)  climbed 10.66 points, or 0.3
percent, to 4,016.05, gaining for a fifth straight day. The
measure is set for a 4.5 percent jump this week, the steepest
advance since the week ended Sept. 17.  PT Hexindo Adiperkasa (HEXA IJ), the Indonesian unit of
Hitachi Construction Machinery Co., advanced 1.8 percent to
8,450 rupiah. Kontan reported the heavy-equipment distributor
plans to pay 40 percent of last year’s net income as a dividend
in October. Corporate Secretary Heri Akhyar couldn’t be reached
when called at his office.  PT International Nickel  Indonesia  (INCO IJ), the nation’s
biggest producer of the metal, fell 1.3 percent to 3,950 rupiah,
the first drop in five days. Nickel futures declined as much as
2.2 percent to $21,600 a metric ton in  London .  PT Trada Maritime (TRAM IJ), a provider of marine services
to the  petroleum industry , jumped 14 percent to 990 rupiah, set
for a record close. Trada Maritime signed a memorandum of
understanding to acquire convertible bonds issued by PT Awesome
Coal that will allow it to own a  coal mine  with reserves of 61
million tons in East Kalimantan province, Trada Maritime said in
an e-mailed statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Berni Moestafa in Jakarta at 
 bmoestafa@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Darren Boey at 
 dboey@bloomberg.net  